.TH "s3c_hwmon_create_attr" 9 "s3c_hwmon_create_attr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
s3c_hwmon_create_attr \- create hwmon attribute for given channel.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" s3c_hwmon_create_attr
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct s3c_hwmon_chcfg *cfg "  ","
.BI "struct s3c_hwmon_attr *attrs "  ","
.BI "int channel "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
The device to create the attribute on.
.IP "cfg" 12
The channel configuration passed from the platform data.
.IP "attrs" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "channel" 12
The ADC channel number to process.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create the scaled attribute for use with hwmon from the specified
platform data in \fIpdata\fP. The sysfs entry is handled by the routine
\fBs3c_hwmon_ch_show\fP.

The attribute name is taken from the configuration data if present
otherwise the name is taken by concatenating in_ with the channel
number.
